3E%3Cstrong%3E'Namaste'%2C%20Starmer%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20days%20of%20the%20election%20campaign%2C%20Keir%20Starmer%20visited%20the%20Shree%20Swaminarayan%20Mandir%20Kingsbury%2C%20a%20prominent%20Hindu%20temple%20in%20London%2C%20and%20said%20%26quot%3Bnamaste%26quot%3B%20with%20folded%20hands.%20His%20charm%20offensive%20included%20him%20wearing%20a%20%3Cem%3Etilak%20%3C%2Fem%3Eon%20his%20forehead%20and%20a%20floral%20garland%20around%20his%20neck.%20Starmer%20may%20have%20looked%20out%20of%20place%2C%20but%20it%20was%20an%20attempt%20to%20placate%20angry%20Indian%20diaspora%20voters%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20whom%20were%20expected%20to%20favour%20the%20Conservative%20Party.%20The%20temple%20visit%20was%20also%20intended%20to%20send%20out%20a%20strong%20signal%20of%20friendship%20with%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fuk-election-results-live-rishi-sunak-braces-for-huge-loss-as-early-results-herald-labour-keir-starmer-win-6037190%5C%22%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%C2%A0Labour%20Sweeps%20UK%20Polls%2C%20Rishi%20Sunak's%20Party%20Ousted%20For%201st%20Time%20In%2014%20Years%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20his%20awkwardness%2C%20Starmer%20knew%20he%20had%20to%20perform%20this%20political%20act%2C%20not%20only%20because%20his%20visit%20underscored%20Labour's%20commitment%20to%20embracing%20and%20celebrating%20diversity%20within%20the%20UK%2C%20but%20also%20because%20he%20needed%20to%20repair%20relations%20with%20the%20influential%20Indian%20diaspora%2C%20and%2C%20by%20extension%2C%20India.%20It%20had%20been%20clear%20for%20quite%20some%20time%20that%20his%20party%20was%20returning%20to%20power%20after%20a%20hiatus%20of%2014%20years%20and%20he%20was%20going%20to%20be%20the%20next%20UK%20Prime%20Minister%3B%20that%20is%20why%20he%20needed%20to%20undertake%20an%20India%20outreach%20before%20assuming%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Baggage%20Of%20The%20Past%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarmer's%20gesture%20of%20visiting%20the%20temple%20was%20particularly%20significant%20given%20the%20events%20of%20September%202019%2C%20when%20during%20its%20annual%20conference%20in%20Brighton%2C%20the%20Labour%20Party%20under%20Jeremy%20Corbyn's%20leadership%20had%20passed%20a%20motion%20addressing%20the%20situation%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20The%20motion%20declared%20that%20there%20was%20a%20humanitarian%20crisis%20in%20the%20region%20and%20asserted%20that%20the%20people%20of%20Kashmir%20should%20be%20granted%20the%20right%20to%20self-determination.%20Additionally%2C%20it%20had%20called%20for%20the%20deployment%20of%20international%20monitors%20to%20the%20area%20to%20ensure%20the%20protection%20of%20human%20rights%20and%20the%20assessment%20of%20the%20situation%20on%20the%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENeedless%20to%20say%2C%20the%20Labour%20Party%20had%20gone%20too%20far.%20And%20despite%20the%20clarification%20issued%20by%20Jeremy%20Corbyn%2C%20the%20damage%20was%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20motion%20was%20met%20with%20significant%20backlash%20from%20the%20Indian%20diaspora%2C%20who%20felt%20that%20it%20was%20one-sided%20and%20did%20not%20consider%20the%20complexities%20of%20the%20Kashmir%20issue.%20The%20event%20marked%20a%20turning%20point%20as%20many%20members%20of%20the%20Indian%20community%20began%20to%20shift%20their%20allegiances%20to%20the%20Conservative%20Party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fthis-is-a-massacre-conservative-leader-as-labour-heads-for-massive-uk-win-6037516%5C%22%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%C2%A0%26quot%3BThis%20Is%20A%20Massacre%26quot%3B%3A%20Conservative%20Leader%20As%20Labour%20Heads%20For%20Massive%20UK%20Win%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20government%20also%20responded%20sharply%20to%20the%20Labour's%20motion.%20It%20was%20reported%20that%20the%20Indian%20High%20Commission%20in%20London%20took%20the%20unprecedented%20step%20of%20cancelling%20a%20scheduled%20dinner%20for%20Labour%20leaders%2C%20signalling%20its%20strong%20disapproval.%20The%20Indian%20government%20officially%20rejected%20the%20motion%2C%20emphasising%20its%20concerns%20about%20what%20it%20viewed%20as%20interference%20in%20its%20internal%20affairs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20effort%20to%20mend%20relations%2C%20Starmer%20attempted%20to%20address%20the%20situation%20last%20year%2C%20when%20he%20asserted%20that%20the%20Labour%20Party%20would%20strive%20to%20maintain%20strong%20relations%20with%20India%2C%20indicating%20a%20desire%20to%20rebuild%20trust%20and%20cooperation.%20Despite%20these%20efforts%2C%20the%20episode%20highlighted%20the%20fragile%20nature%20of%20Labour's%20relations%20with%20India%20and%20underscored%20the%20significant%20political%20influence%20of%20the%20Indian%20diaspora%20in%20the%20UK.%3Cbr%3E%5CnLabour's%20image%20makeover%20under%20Starmer%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Changed%20Labour%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20the%20Labour%20Party%20has%20now%20made%20a%20triumphant%20comeback%2C%20securing%20a%20thumping%20majority.%20We%20should%20keep%20in%20mind%20that%20the%20party%20is%20a%20much-changed%20one%20under%20Starmer.%20It%20wants%20to%20inject%20more%20depth%20and%20substance%20into%20Britain's%20strategic%20partnership%20with%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20is%20most%20likely%20to%20carefully%20monitor%20Labour's%20policy%20stance%20on%20Kashmir%2C%20immigration%20and%20the%20proposed%20Free%20Trade%20Agreement%20(FTA).%20The%20Indian%20government%20may%20have%20apprehensions%20about%20Labour's%20views%20on%20its%20internal%20matters%2C%20but%20on%20balance%2C%20the%20India-UK%20bilateral%20relations%20will%20not%20change%20much%20under%20Starmer.%20In%20fact%2C%20Labour%20supporters%20in%20the%20Indian%20community%20believe%20that%20under%20him%2C%20the%20relations%20are%20likely%20to%20improve.%20It%20is%20being%20claimed%20that%20the%20number%20of%20Indian-origin%20Labour%20MPs%20would%20double%20from%20the%20current%20six%20members%20in%20the%20outgoing%20Parliament.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWill%20The%20Ties%20Improve%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAcademics%20in%20the%20UK%20at%20times%20tend%20to%20romanticise%20the%20bilateral%20ties%20between%20the%20two%20countries%2C%20looking%20at%20it%20chiefly%20from%20the%20prism%20of%20colonial%20nostalgia.%20We%20are%20led%20to%20believe%20that%20it%20is%20in%20India's%20interest%20to%20have%20a%20deeper%20strategic%20partnership%20with%20Britain.%20To%20be%20honest%2C%20however%2C%20India%20sees%20Britain%20as%20a%20middle%20power%2C%20whose%20influence%20on%20the%20global%20stage%20has%20been%20on%20the%20wane%20for%20long.%20One%20can%20only%20blame%20the%20Conservative%20Party%20for%20it%2C%20a%20beleaguered%20and%20divided%20house%20which%20presided%20over%2014%20years%20of%20stagnation.%20India%20under%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20who%20was%20born%20after%20the%20country's%20independence%2C%20is%2C%20whether%20rightly%20or%20wrongly%2C%20not%20in%20awe%20of%20its%20erstwhile%20colonial%20masters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fuks-labour-party-commits-to-stamping-out-anti-india-sentiments-5997729%5C%22%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%C2%A0UK's%20Labour%20Party%20Commits%20To%20Stamping%20Out%20%26quot%3BAnti-India%20Sentiments%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20the%20bilateral%20trade%20in%20goods%20and%20services%20is%20growing%20steadily%2C%20and%20stood%20at%C2%A0%C2%A339%20billion%20last%20year%2C%20with%20the%20balance%20of%20trade%20heavily%20in%20India's%20favour.%20Yes%2C%20we%20have%20a%20vocal%2C%20upwardly%20mobile%20Indian%20diaspora%2C%20which%20acts%20as%20a%20bridge%20between%20the%20two%20countries%20and%20it%20often%20works%20to%20India's%20advantage.%20But%20the%20oomph%20factor%20in%20bilateral%20relations%20has%20been%20missing%20for%20a%20long%20time.%20For%20example%2C%20India%20and%20the%20US%20warmed%20up%20to%20each%20other%20and%20became%20trusted%20partners%20only%20after%20the%20Civil%20Nuclear%20Agreement%20between%20the%20two%20countries%20was%20brokered%20under%20President%20George%20W.%20Bush.%20It%20was%20a%20pivotal%20moment%20that%20added%20significant%20%26quot%3Boomph%26quot%3B%20to%20bilateral%20ties%20and%20transformed%20the%20dynamics%20of%20the%20relationship%2C%20fostering%20deeper%20strategic%2C%20economic%2C%20and%20technological%20cooperation.%20It%20set%20the%20stage%20for%20an%20enduring%20partnership%20in%20the%2021st%20century.%20Even%20during%20the%20Obama%20and%20Trump%20administrations%20the%20bilateral%20ties%20never%20ran%20out%20of%20excitement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20cannot%20say%20the%20same%20about%20India-UK%20relations%2C%20which%20badly%20need%20to%20be%20injected%20with%20energy%2C%20excitement%20and%20a%20mega-deal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFTA%3A%20Starmer's%20First%20Challenge%20In%20India-UK%20Ties%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20regards%20to%20India%2C%20one%20of%20the%20first%20tasks%20on%20Starmer's%20desk%20will%20be%20to%20reach%20a%20Free%20Trade%20Agreement.%20He%20has%20maintained%20his%20commitment%20to%20completing%20the%20FTA%2C%20but%20it%20is%20not%20going%20to%20be%20easy.%20India's%20priority%20appears%20to%20be%20to%20finalise%20an%20agreement%20with%20the%20European%20Union%20(EU)%20first.%20The%20bilateral%20trade%20in%20goods%20and%20services%20last%20year%20stood%20at%20%E2%82%AC113%C2%A0billion.%20The%20two%20sides%20relaunched%20the%20negotiations%20in%202022%20and%20the%20progress%20is%20said%20to%20be%20satisfactory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20group%20of%20researchers%2C%20another%20stumbling%20block%20in%20the%20India-UK%20FTA%20is%20%26quot%3Bthe%20opposition%20in%20the%20UK%20to%20Indian%20demands%20for%20more%20visas%20for%20intra-company%20transfers%20and%20particularly%20to%20demands%20that%20social%20security%20contributions%20from%20Indian%20workers%20during%20such%20transfers%20be%20reimbursed%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EImmigration%20Policies%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBrexit%20has%20led%20to%20record%20levels%20of%20Indian%20immigration.%20Of%20the%206.85%20lakh%20immigrants%20in%20the%20UK%20today%2C%20the%20majority%20come%20from%20India.%20The%20Labour%20Party's%20stated%20aim%20is%20to%20reduce%20legal%20immigration%20and%20curb%20illegal%20immigration.%20Many%20of%20the%20legal%20Indian%20immigrants%20are%20IT%20professionals%20on%20work%20permits%2C%20contributing%20to%20the%20UK's%20technology%20sector.%20There%20is%20a%20small%20number%20of%20illegal%20immigrants%20from%20India%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20party's%20policy%20seeks%20to%20balance%20the%20economic%20benefits%20of%20skilled%20migrants%20with%20the%20goal%20of%20controlling%20overall%20immigration%20numbers%2C%20reflecting%20broader%20political%20and%20economic%20priorities.%3Cbr%3E%5CnHuman%20Rights%20and%20Citizenship%20Laws%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHistorically%2C%20the%20Labour%20Party%20has%20been%20vocal%20about%20human%20rights%20issues%20in%20India%2C%20particularly%20on%20laws%20like%20the%20Citizenship%20(Amendment)%20Act%20(CAA)%20and%20the%20National%20Register%20of%20Citizens%20(NRC).%20The%20Labour%20Party's%20criticism%20has%20been%20viewed%20by%20the%20Indian%20government%20as%20interference%20and%20a%20misrepresentation%20of%20India's%20internal%20policies%20aimed%20at%20addressing%20specific%20security%20concerns.%20Starmer%20will%20be%20under%20pressure%20from%20domestic%20human%20rights%20organisations%20to%20put%20forward%20liberal%20British%20perspectives.%20His%20diplomatic%20skills%20are%20bound%20to%20be%20tested%20in%20the%20coming%20months%20and%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20relations%20between%20the%20UK's%20Labour%20Party%20and%20the%20Indian%20government%20are%20complex%2C