ers%20from%20the%20Royal%20Veterinary%20College%20made%20the%20discovery%20when%20viewing%20video%20footage%20of%20hippos%20romping%20around%20a%20theme%20park%20in%20North%20Yorkshire%2C%20England.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20pleasantly%20surprised%20to%20see%20how%20hippos%20get%20airborne%20when%20they%20move%20quickly%2C%26quot%3B%20John%20Hutchinson%2C%20an%20RVC%20professor%20of%20evolutionary%20biomechanics%2C%20said%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rvc.ac.uk%2Fresearch%2Fresearch-centres-and-facilities%2Fstructure-and-motion%2Fnews%2Frvc-research-discovers-hippos-ability-to-become-airborne%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20a%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20impressive!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225cfd0ca2-94e5-4192-8437-3cf9f4f1f574%5C%22%3EHippos%20move%20more%20like%20horses%20than%20elephants%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20blurry%20image%20of%20a%20hippo%20running%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66872834268f62ba18a79226%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22724%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFor%20a%20glorious%200.3%20seconds%2C%20some%20hippos%20lift%20all%20four%20feet%20off%20the%20ground.%3Cp%3EJohan%20Vermeulen%2FRoyal%20Veterinary%20College%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20elephants%20walk%2C%20they%20move%20their%20back%20left%20leg%2C%20front%20left%20leg%2C%20back%20right%20leg%2C%20then%20front%20right%20leg%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc51y714jy91o%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20BBC%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Scientists%20thought%20hippos%20moved%20in%20a%20similar%20way%20because%20of%20their%20enormous%20size.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20when%20Hutchinson%20and%20RVC%20undergraduate%20student%20Emily%20Pringle%20watched%20footage%20of%20two%20hippos%20at%20Flamingo%20Land%2C%20the%20theme%20park